text: Dendropsophus counani is a frog that lives in Brazil, French Guiana, Suriname, and Guyana. The adult male frog is 19.6 to 21.7 mm long from nose to rear end and the adult female frog is 22.1 to 24.5 mm. The tops of the back legs are dark grey with some white. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
